Package org.trikkle

Class Link

java.lang.Object
org.trikkle.Link
All Implemented Interfaces:
Congruent<Link>
public final class Link extends Object implements Congruent<Link>
Analogous to an adjacency list entry in a graph, except there are multiple input nodes and output nodes. It is actually a directed hypergraph.
Since:
0.1.0

    • Link

      public Link(Arc arc)
      Create a link with the given arc. The dependency and output node are generated from the arc via Arc.getInputDatumNames() and Arc.getOutputDatumNames(). All input datums will be added to a single dependency node, and all output datums will be added to a single output node. The nodes created will either be a DiscreteNode or an EmptyNode, if there are no datums.

      This constructor is ideal for graphs without partial dependencies- that is, an arc that only uses a subset of the datums of its dependency.

      Parameters:
      arc - the arc of the link
      See Also:
      • Input
      • Output
      • Arc.getInputDatumNames()
      • Arc.getOutputDatumNames()
